The paper uses deep reinforcement learning to optimize the scheduling of clinical tests for adverse event forecasting, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also addresses the issue of cost reduction and patient discomfort, which could be categorized under computer engineering (cs.CE) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper deals with real-world clinical datasets, which could be categorized under social and information sciences (cs.SI).
